# Naming Conventions

- Follow Google C++ style as the baseline.
- **函数与方法：小驼峰** — all free functions, member functions, and static methods use lower camelCase (`makeServer`, `registerWith`, `parseOptions`).
- **变量：小驼峰** — local variables, parameters, and struct / aggregate fields use lower camelCase (`localVar`, `playbackPath`, `deviceKindsProvider`).
- **成员：小驼峰 + 尾部下划线** — class data members use lower camelCase with a trailing underscore (`memberName_`, `ioContext_`, `progressMutex_`).
- Project globals use lower camelCase with a `g` prefix (`gLogger`, `gCursor`). Do not rename generated or third-party APIs (e.g. protobuf `time_sec()`, `FLAGS_log_level`).
- Production file names use lowercase letters only and do not use underscores.
- Unit test file names must be `<corresponding_file_name>_test.cpp`.
- All header files use `#pragma once` only; do not use include guards.
- Apply naming consistently to new files and refactors.

## Examples

```cpp
// Good
int readEvents();
bool openOutput(const std::string& path);
void registerWith(Ioc& ioc);
```

```text
// Good file names
inputdevice.cpp
filesystem.h
evdevlinux.cpp
inputdevice_test.cpp
argparser_test.cpp
```

